"PCI DSS has been a controversial subject for businesses and organisations in the western world for some time. There have been many complaints from a number of sources over the past few years over the exacting requirements that PCI DSS imposes on organisations that need to take card payments in order to sell their products. From the large global online retailers such as Amazon, to the small ecommerce companies attempting to make it in a volatile economy, all are required to comply with PCI DSS and many – unfortunately – do not understand it."
